<html><body><h2>What is MATE?</h2>
MATE is a fork of GNOME 2.

It provides an intuitive and attractive desktop to Linux users using traditional metaphors.



<img class=" " alt="" src="http://library.gnome.org/misc/release-notes/2.32/figures/gnome-2-32.png.en_GB" width="432" height="270"> Gnome 2.32

<h2>Where does the name come from?</h2>

The name "MATE" comes from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yerba_mate">yerba maté</a>, a species of holly native to subtropical South America. Its leaves contain caffeine and are used to make infusions and a beverage called mate.



<img class="  " alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Ilex_paraguariensis_-_K%C3%B6hler%E2%80%93s_Medizinal-Pflanzen-074.jpg/220px-Ilex_paraguariensis_-_K%C3%B6hler%E2%80%93s_Medizinal-Pflanzen-074.jpg" width="154" height="223"> Yerba Maté

